Contact






The foundation of what sets Cure apart from the competition is its proprietary and patent pending Tri-Active system. This composition begins with a liquid based film layer that contains and stabilizes the active ingredients. The second component of the composition is a powder matrix layer that can deliver additional active ingredients and provides many functional qualities, including: extra flavoring ingredients, pliability enhancers, mucosal permeation enhancers, and improved stability.
		

Expand
Close





Advances in Technology
Delivery Systems
Intellectual Property




Utilizing our Tri-Active film matrix, Pharmaceutical companies may be able to extend the patent life cycles as well as create a new family of patent protection. The opportunity for the Tri-Active film matrix is substantial; our Tri-Active drug delivery can be applied to a large pool of drugs due to its ability to carry a variety of active pharmaceutical ingredients with higher pay loads.

The Tri-Active film matrix is more stable, durable with the ability to augment the dissolution rate, with a quicker dissolution than other dosage forms.  The technology enables differentiation within large therapeutic categories and potentially improves patient compliance. In addition, the sublingual and buccal delivery of a given drug via the Tri-Active film has the potential to improve the onset of action, lower dosing and enhance the efficacy thereby widening the therapeutic index.

		    

Cure has developed a portfolio of drug platform delivery systems to include; 

Multi-layer oral thin film (OTF)
Proprietary liquid based encapsulation technologies
Transdermal (skin) delivery
Buccal (gland) delivery
Gastrointestinal delivery systems

Cure's R&D team is further developing new and innovative ways to deliver drugs more efficiently.

		    

Pharmaceutical companies are becoming increasingly focused on product life cycle management due to expiring patents, generic encroachment and declining new drug pipelines.  It is estimated that over 80 major drugs representing over 95 billion in sales will lose patent or exclusivity protection by 2015.

CURE's IP development strategy focuses on improving product integrity, efficiency and load capacity for all drug delivery technologies.  CURE has protected these innovations using a blended strategy of patents, trade secrets and proprietary equipment design.

Components of Cure's IP Portfolio:

Film compositions
Polymers
Taste formulations
Process engineering
Packaging










